[1] Cholera - Iran (southern provinces)
Date: 20 Jun 2011
Source: Trend [edited]
http://en.trend.az/news/society/1894061.html


Some 13 people have been infected with cholera in Iran, Disease
Management Center director Hossein Masoumi Asl was quoted as saying by
iribnews.ir. He said the necessary precautions are being taken, and in
general, their condition is satisfactory.

He said the infection cases mainly were revealed in the Iranian
provinces of Sistan-Baluchistan, Fars, Khuzestan, and Hormuzgan.
Doctors took samples from relatives of ill persons, but no infection
was found.

The country has been recording cases of cholera infection for nearly
45 years, he said. The number of such cases was 15 in 2010. Asl said
cholera has not spread throughout the country.

--
