[2] Cholera - Afghanistan (Zabul)
Date: Thu 18 Jun 2011
Source: Channel 6 News Online [edited]
http://channel6newsonline.com/2011/06/cholera-outbreak-in-southeast-afghanistan-kills-14/


A sudden outbreak of cholera in south eastern Afghanistan has killed
at least 14 people and infected dozens more, local media reported. The
Pajhwok Afghan News (PAN) agency reported that the epidemic in
southern Zabul province broke out earlier this week, infecting at
least 84 people. 14 of them have died, according to deputy governor
Mohammad Jan Rasulyar.

Few details about the outbreak in the remote area were immediately
available, but a spokesperson for the NATO-led International Security
Assistance Force (ISAF) said it airlifted several locals in relation
to the outbreak.

"ISAF did air transport 5 local nationals with dehydration symptoms,"
the spokesperson said. "It has not been confirmed if they are infected
with cholera. The [Ministry of Health] has the lead in this matter."

--
