[3] Cholera, contaminated water - China (Hong Kong SAR)
Date: Fri 19 Jun 2011
Source: The Examiner [edited]
http://www.examiner.com/infectious-disease-in-national/cholera-found-hong-kong-restaurant-fish-tank


The Hong Kong Food and Environmental Hygiene Department on Friday 19
Jun 2011 confirmed [the presence of] cholera in a water sample from a
fish tank at Queens Road Central restaurant.

The restaurant, Hei Yuet Restaurant, was ordered immediately and
temporarily to close for thorough disinfection after _Vibrio cholerae_
O1 El Tor serotype Ogawa was detected in the restaurant fish tank.

According to health officials, the restaurant will remain closed for
thorough cleansing and disinfection of the premises and fish tanks
until the director is satisfied with the overall hygiene condition of
the premises and that there is no immediate health hazard.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is not the 1st time ProMED-mail has had reported this type of
event. Hong Kong usually reports a handful of cases of cholera each
year, primarily but not exclusively imported. - Mod.LL

