[5] Cholera - Niger (Southern Region)
Date: Sat 18 Jun 2011
Source: The Vanguard [edited]
http://www.vanguardngr.com/2011/06/cholera-kills-6-in-niger/


Cholera has killed at least 6 of the 347 known cases in Niger,
particularly in Niamey and Tillabery, the Nigerien minister of health,
Soumana Sanda, has said.

Several isolation camps for patients have been built in the Gamkalle
district of Niamey, in the rural town of Libore and N'Dounga, the
areas most affected by the disease.

